<plot>During the Canadian winter, what does it take to go to the road and check your mail box? A fire blazes in a fireplace; a solitary man dresses, putting on layer after layer. He goes outside - it's snowing and the wind is blowing. He has to scrape snow and ice off the car. To start the car, he has to hook up the battery to that of another vehicle, then, tires spinning he heads for the road. More adventures await. How many fingers will he lose to frostbite?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?017387</url></doc>
